issues.title: unfinished workrave feature
issues.body: finish to implement the workrave feature

issues.title: close button doesn't works all the time
issues.body: The main productivity interface (conf) has a close button which doesn't seems to work all the times after to press "start work", it happens most of the "first run" times there (dual screen?)

issues.title: After restart, windows are in the wrong desktop
issues.body: By some reason e17 restarted when switching desktops (i suppose that prod. restarted it by some reason), after this happened, all my non-worktools windows are minimized to the first desktop, so they forgot on which desktop was originally, I suppose that this bug can be reproduced by simply trigger a restart of e17

commit.message: prepared edje file for include text
Clean up, Added eina_unused for unused vars

Use standard E function to check config version compatibility.

The open coded version of the check was incorrect anyway.

Add meaningful module descritption to the module.desktop.in

Also drop useless translations imported from the skeleton module.

Remove translations imported from skeleton module.

They has different messages, and it's easier for translators to start
from the clean pot than update different translation.

remove use of AM_PROG_CC_STDC as AC_PROG_CC does it. & autotools: move to AC_CONFIG_HEADERS.

updated version setup from hex to dec
Fixed break timer, disable some annoying Debug logs
Lets save data on change, instead on "close", this might fix the close hang
clean up unused variables, thanks to -Wall

added sound when breaktime, custom configs

added a notification sound when breaktime is reached

also changed some default configurations
track window by Ecore_X_Window instead of pid_t, disabled e_mod_log_cb, seems it never worked
fixed bug: E_BORDER_NULL, trying to control enlightenment closed dialog
clicking on productivity icon on a shelf now opens the settings panel
implemented: DPMS, if the screen is blank, pause the main functions, break and manager
only track property change if urgent is true
fixed: unable to add keybinding while productivity is running
save instantly instead of queue, also save on close button
play another extra "click" when its at 15 seconds before...
only track event when start is pressed

removed old functions

	modified:   e_mod_config_windows.c
	modified:   e_mod_main.c
wow, working state of urgent windows, remember disabled

removed old manager function, and others, fix urgent window not hiding after start/stop work button is pressed

	modified:   e_mod_config_windows.c
play sound twice to warn user break is about to over
fixed: window does not unhide in break time
Readme filled up with TODO and details
implemented beep 5 secs before break is finished

added mp3 data file to install with makeinstall

This small commit can be used as an example of how to add files in your
"installed system" by using Makefile.am / configure.ac
fixed: when you move a window to the other screen,  productivity puts it back to the previous one., and urgent segf when exit
fixed "Minutes of Work" not being disabled when e17 restarts and work is set to "Start working"
fixed stop clock hour incorrect value
implement allow user to see urgent window, but when you focus out it will be hidden
start stop activates window manager, no longer need to wait for event
removed "OK" and "APPLY", start/stop working saves the data now
fixed unhide, when added a new work-tool after you "started work"
match name by class also, this should fix firefox/iceweasel
worktools should update correctly now, instead having to reload the module to get the updated list
updated break $x time to 30min max and $y time to 360min max
if we cant find .desktop file close app, send log to INF
implemented function to clean up the remember list
less annoying DBG code in _EVENT_ use EVENT_DBG()
fixed but with window always hidden from pager, and unable to focus window
hidden windows now remember which desktop they were hidden from and unhides correctly
fixed segf related to printf argv[0], when argv is not set
if lock=1, disable edit-mode from start/stop clock
rmeove argv[0] INF/printf, if not initialized this causes e17 to freeze while running another e17 in Xephyr
Use default gettext definition, _("") not D_("")
Added e_mod_log.c to makefile.am, register logger to module
Added eina log domain callback function
Started with a clean renaming of skel emodule
First import from skel code, r74950
